      "comment_id" : 70714266,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "This will not work without a warning if there are further templates involved. E.g. <code>someMethod(someList.toArray(new ArrayList&lt;Something&gt;[someList.size()]))</code> will give you a warning that is very annoying if the function is more than a few lines long (because you can either suppress it for the whole function or you have to create the array in an additional step and suppress the warning on the variable you store it."
